The paper focuses on speech act detection in conversations about bug repair, which is a topic within software engineering (cs.SE). The use of manual annotation and supervised learning algorithms suggests a focus on natural language processing (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The application of virtual assistants in software engineering also suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the use of data and experiments suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR).
